Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to
a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and
tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @skin-on salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with
@sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or pork for salmon.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add salmon and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer salmon to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add 1/4 cup water,
@peach jam{1%unit}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and juice from half the
lemon. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced and thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{2%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Return salmon to pan and turn a few times to coat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Toss green beans with lemon zest.

Divide rice, green beans, and salmon between plates. Spoon any remaining
sauce from pan over salmon. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.